casebody.data:
STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
James L. CANADA, Appellant. WD 80362 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: October 2, 2018 Nathan J. Aquino, Jefferson City, MO, for respondent. Irene C. Karns, Columbia, MO, for appellant. Before Division One: Thomas H. Newton, Presiding Judge, Gary D. Witt, Judge and Anthony Rex Gabbert, Judge

ORDER

Per curiam:

James L. Canada, Jr. ("Canada"), appeals his convictions of four counts of first degree statutory sodomy, section 566.062; two counts of first degree statutory rape, section 566.032; six counts of incest, section 568.020; and two counts of child molestation in the first degree, section 566.067. Following a jury trial, the court sentenced Canada to a total of 75 years' imprisonment. We affirm. Rule 30.25(b).
